list.s: LT. AMY BRANNIGAN Sir, my orders are to bring you to the base.

s.comment: idiomatic: in order to, as a means to; with the purpose of

list.s: If the equity argument under the Necessary and Proper Clause justifies extension of the copyright for those whose copyright will expire tomorrow if it's not extended, in order to put them on parity with those getting copyrights for new works, why doesn't it apply to the copyright, the holder of the copyright that expired yesterday?

s.comment: idiomatic: in order to, as a means to; with the purpose of

list.s: [crewmen are whipped, in order to turn a large screw that raises the Kraken summoning device]

s.comment: a command, but not one given by a superior as in sense #1

list.s: [Hadrus' head lies on the ground, attempting to give orders to the rest of his body to find the head]
